{"actual_usd":0.12548,"character_id":"b01cbfb8-15e7-473f-80f5-6e3e210d14c1","character_name":"Maisie Rourke","completion_tokens":206,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24478,"reply":"\"No—neither of those quite tells it true.\" *I brush a little flour off my apron and lean one hip against the counter, thinking how to keep the loaf from collapsing in the middle.* \"Not three gods, and not one God changing costumes.\"\n\n\"The way I was taught it, and I think that's true more or less, is this: one God, truly one, and yet the Father, the Son, and the Holy Spirit are each fully God—distinct, not interchangeable.\" *I twirl that gray-streaked strand once between my fingers.* \"That water picture sounds handy, but it slips into saying God is one thing wearing three forms at different times. And that misses something important, because the Son prays to the Father, and the Spirit isn't just another mask pulled on after.\"\n\n\"It's a big invisible thing, so every comparison limps.\" *The brick oven gives off a steady warmth at my side.* \"But if you want, I can try the plain-English version next.\"","rolling_24h_usd":40.801975000000034,"run_id":"3048f80a-4155-47b8-be19-b732cdd593bf"}
